## 1. The Winning Formula

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  SPECIFIC PROBLEM  +  FOCUSED MVP  +  SMOOTH DEMO  +  COMPELLING PITCH  │
│       (30%)              (25%)           (20%)            (25%)          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### The 3 Golden Rules

| Rule | Description | Why It Wins |
|------|-------------|-------------|
| **Niche > Broad** | "Reduce food waste in university canteens" beats "Fix climate change" | Judges reward specificity and feasibility |
| **Working > Perfect** | A polished 2-feature demo beats a buggy 10-feature prototype | Live demos > slide decks, always |
| **Story > Code** | Teams that explain *why* they built it win over teams that explain *how* | Emotional connection drives decisions |

---

## 2. Problem Statement Selection Framework

### Step 1: The UNIQUE Score (Rate 1-5 for each)

Use this scoring matrix to evaluate any problem statement:

| Criteria | Question | Weight |
|----------|----------|--------|
| **U** — Underexplored | Has this been done 100 times on Devpost? (Lower = better) | 20% |
| **N** — Need (Real Pain) | Is there a real person/community suffering from this? | 25% |
| **I** — Impact Breadth | Does it touch social + economic + environmental dimensions? | 20% |
| **Q** — Quick to Demo | Can you build a compelling MVP in 24-48 hours? | 15% |
| **U** — Uses Modern Tech | Does it leverage AI agents, edge AI, IoT, or emerging tech? | 10% |
| **E** — Excites the Team | Will the team stay energized at 3 AM working on this? | 10% |

> [!TIP]
> **Threshold:** Only proceed with problem statements scoring **≥ 3.5/5 overall**. Anything below is too risky.

### Step 2: The "Triple Impact" Filter

Every winning problem statement should hit **at least 2 of 3**:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Your Problem Statement] --> B{Social Impact?}
    A --> C{Economic Impact?}
    A --> D{Environmental Impact?}
    B --> E[✅ Improves lives, reduces inequality, empowers communities]
    C --> F[✅ Creates jobs, saves money, enables new markets]
    D --> G[✅ Reduces waste, conserves resources, fights climate change]
    E --> H[🏆 WINNING ZONE: Hit 2+ of these]
    F --> H
    G --> H
```

### Step 3: The "3-Sentence Pitch Test"

Before committing, your idea must pass this test:

> **"[Target user] struggles with [specific problem]. Our solution uses [technology] to [specific action]. This will [measurable impact]."**

**Example:**
> "Rural health workers in India struggle to diagnose skin diseases without dermatologist access. Our solution uses an on-device AI model running on cheap Android phones to identify 15 common skin conditions from a photo. This will reduce misdiagnosis by 60% in areas with no specialist within 100km."

If you can't fill in all blanks clearly → **pivot the idea**.

