## 6. Hackathon Participation Playbook

### Phase 0: Pre-Hackathon (1-2 weeks before)

```
□ Research the theme, sponsors, and past winners
□ Form a balanced team: 2 devs + 1 designer + 1 pitcher/domain expert
□ Set up dev environment: GitHub repo, CI/CD, deployment pipeline
□ Pre-research 3-5 problem statements using this guide
□ Identify sponsor APIs/tools and build basic familiarity
□ Prepare a "template" project with auth, UI framework, and DB ready
```

### Phase 1: First 15% — Ideation (Hours 0-4)

```
□ List 5 problem statements
□ Score each using the UNIQUE framework (Section 2)
□ Apply the 3-Sentence Pitch Test
□ Select ONE problem statement (commitment!)
□ Define the MVP scope: exactly 2-3 core features
□ Sketch the UI on paper (5 screens max)
□ Divide responsibilities clearly among team members
```

### Phase 2: Middle 65% — Build Sprint (Hours 4-30)

```
□ Set up the project structure and database schema
□ Build core feature #1 (the demo-worthy one)
□ Build core feature #2
□ Integrate APIs and external data sources
□ Focus on the "happy path" — make it work for the demo scenario
□ Start UI polish at the 60% mark, not the end
□ Commit often, deploy to a live URL early
```

### Phase 3: Final 20% — Polish & Pitch (Hours 30-48)

```
□ Fix the top 3 bugs that would embarrass you in a demo
□ Polish the UI — consistent colors, fonts, spacing
□ Prepare a 3-minute demo script
□ Build your pitch deck (5 slides max):
    1. The Problem (with real data)
    2. The Solution (live demo)
    3. How It Works (architecture diagram)
    4. Impact & Scalability
    5. Team & Next Steps
□ Rehearse the pitch 3 times
□ Prepare for 5 likely judge questions
□ Sleep for at least 2 hours (seriously)
```

### The 5-Slide Pitch Template

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  SLIDE 1: THE PROBLEM                       │
│  "X million people face [problem]..."        │
│  Show a real statistic or personal story     │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  SLIDE 2: LIVE DEMO                         │
│  Switch to the actual app. Show the          │
│  "wow moment" in under 90 seconds.           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  SLIDE 3: HOW IT WORKS                      │
│  Clean architecture diagram.                 │
│  Mention specific tech & why.                │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  SLIDE 4: IMPACT                            │
│  Social + Economic + Environmental metrics   │
│  "This could save X lives / $Y / Z tons CO₂" │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  SLIDE 5: TEAM + NEXT STEPS                 │
│  30-day roadmap. Ask for the win.            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

