## 7. Quick Decision Tree for Any Hackathon

Use this when the hackathon announces its theme:

```mermaid
graph TD
    START[Hackathon Theme Announced] --> Q1{Does it have a<br/>specific theme?}
    
    Q1 -->|Yes| Q2{Which domain?}
    Q1 -->|No / Open| OPEN[Use Tier 1 Ideas<br/>from Section 4]
    
    Q2 -->|Healthcare| HC[Focus on: Accessibility,<br/>Offline-first, Rural health]
    Q2 -->|AI/GenAI| AI[Focus on: Multi-agent<br/>orchestration, Edge AI,<br/>Explainability]
    Q2 -->|Sustainability| SUS[Focus on: Water quality,<br/>E-waste, Soil carbon,<br/>Microgrid optimization]
    Q2 -->|Fintech| FIN[Focus on: Informal economy<br/>identity, Microinsurance,<br/>Farmer credit access]
    Q2 -->|Education| EDU[Focus on: Sign language,<br/>Offline tutoring, Media literacy]
    Q2 -->|Social Good| SOC[Focus on: Disaster response,<br/>Elder care, Migrant rights]
    
    HC --> SCORE[Score with UNIQUE<br/>framework]
    AI --> SCORE
    SUS --> SCORE
    FIN --> SCORE
    EDU --> SCORE
    SOC --> SCORE
    OPEN --> SCORE
    
    SCORE --> BUILD[Build the MVP<br/>using the Playbook]
```

### Theme-Specific "Winning Angles"

| If the Theme Is... | The Winning Angle Is... | Avoid This Trap... |
|---------------------|-------------------------|---------------------|
| **AI / GenAI** | Multi-agent systems that *do* things (not just chat) | Building another chatbot wrapper |
| **Healthcare** | Offline-first solutions for underserved populations | Building for rich-country hospitals only |
| **Sustainability** | Infrastructure-level solutions (grids, water, waste systems) | Consumer carbon calculators |
| **Education** | Accessibility + vernacular language support | English-only learning platforms |
| **Fintech** | Serving the unbanked with mobile-first solutions | Crypto trading dashboards |
| **Open Theme** | Triple-impact (social + economic + environmental) problems | Productivity tools for developers |

