## 8. Anti-Patterns — What Loses Hackathons

> [!CAUTION]
> If you catch yourself doing any of these, **stop and pivot immediately**.

### The "Death Traps"

| Anti-Pattern | Why It Loses | What to Do Instead |
|-------------|-------------|---------------------|
| **"Boiling the Ocean"** | Trying to solve world hunger in 48 hours | Solve ONE specific food waste scenario |
| **"Resume-Driven Development"** | Choosing tech to learn, not to solve | Choose boring tech that works, add one "wow" tech |
| **"All Code, No Story"** | Building for 47 hours, pitching for 1 | Allocate 20% of time to pitch prep from the start |
| **"The Feature Factory"** | Building 10 half-working features | Build 2 features that work perfectly |
| **"Solo Hero"** | One person codes, others watch | Divide work: backend, frontend, design, pitch |
| **"Tutorial Project"** | Submitting a customized tutorial/template | Use templates for scaffolding, build the *unique* logic |
| **"Ignoring the Judges"** | Not reading the judging criteria | Literally design your project to score on every criteria |
| **"No User Research"** | "I think this is a problem" with zero evidence | Spend 30 mins finding real data/statistics |

